  "text": "In machine learning-based activity recognition, there have been several different approaches to handling varying sensor positions when trying to identify a user's behavior (e.g. walking, running, climbing stairs). For example, Yang [CITATION_1] addresses different phone positions by projecting data from the accelerometer's x, y, and z axes onto the horizontal and vertical axes to obtain orientation-independent features.",
  "correct_citation": {
